@node pands "ReCatIt / Preferences and Settings Priority"

    PREFERENCES AND SETTINGS PRIORITY

    At the moment, you have three different ways to configure ReCatIt:

        @{" 1 " LINK "tooltypes"} ToolTypes

        @{" 2 " LINK "prefs"} Preference Window

        @{" 3 " LINK "shell"} Shell Parameters


    Of course, there should be a sort of priority for the settings, well, here
    it is:

        1 - ToolTypes are read first

        2 - Prefs are read secondly (and override ToolTypes settings)

        3 - Shell parameters are read at last (and override Prefs)

    
    So, if you configure ReCatIt using ToolTypes, be sure that there is no
    ".prefs" file around.

@endnode

@node shell "ReCatIt / Shell Parameters "

    SHELL PARAMETERS



    ReCatIt can get some parameters from the command line.

    Currently the template is:

    FILENAME,CDEDITOR/S,CATALOGEDITOR/S,CDFILE/S,
    LANGUAGE/K,AUTHOR/K,SD=SMARTDISPLAY/S,AUTOFILL/S

    FILENAME          - Name of the file to load.

    CDEDITOR/S        - If present, ReCatIt will start in Catalog Description ".cd" Mode

    CATALOGEDITOR/S   - If present, ReCatIt will start in Catalog Editor ".catalog" Mode

    CDFILE/S          - If present, ReCatIt will threat the file you have provided as
                        parameter as a ".cd" file and not a ".catalog" file.

    LANGUAGE/K        - Use this keyword to set the default language.

    AUTHOR/K          - Use this keyword to set the default author name.

    SD=SMARTDISPLAY/S - If present, Smart Display Window will be opened at startup.

    AUTOFILL/S        - If present, AutoFill option will be set to on.
                        See @{" Prefs " LINK prefs} for more info.


    Example:

    ReCatIt ReCatIt.cd CDEDITOR CDFILE AUTHOR="Fabio Rotondo" LANGUAGE="italiano"

    Will start ReCatIt in Catalog Description Edit Mode, load the ReCatIt.cd file
    as a ".cd" file and set AUTHOR name and LANGUAGE.


    See @{" Preferences And Settings Priority " LINK "pands"} for further info.
@endnode

@node catinfo "ReCatIt / Catalog Info Window "

    CATALOG INFO WINDOW

    Starting from V2.40, you can ask to ReCatIt to show you all
    the info it has about a file you have loaded.
    This is the use of the Catalog Info Window (shortcut: Amiga + I).

    Inside this window, you'll see all the data related to
    the current catalog in memory.

    If you wish to change these info, use the "Catalog Data" menu.
    See @{" ReCatIt Menus " LINK menu} for more info.


@endnode

@node tooltypes "ReCatIt / Supported ToolTypes "

    TOOLTYPES

    Starting from V2.40, ReCatIt can read ToolTypes.
    At the moment, supported ToolTypes are:

        FONTNAME        - Name of the font for ReCatIt Window
                          Font name *must* end with ".font" extension and 
                          should be written without any brachet (")
                          Ex. FONTNAME=topaz.font

        FONTSIZE        - Size of the font.
                          Ex. FONTSIZE=8

        LANGUAGE        - Default ReCatIt language.
                          Ex. LANGUAGE=italiano

        AUTHOR          - Default ReCatIt author.
                          Ex. AUTHOR=Fabio Rotondo

        SMARTDISPLAY    - If you set this ToolType to TRUE the @{" Smart Display " LINK smartdisp} window
                          will be opened automatically on startup.
                          Ex. SMARTDISPLAY=TRUE

        AUTOFILL        - If you set this to TRUE, the AutoFill option will be
                          turned on. See @{" Prefs " LINK prefs} for more info.
                          Ex. AUTOFILL=TRUE

        XPOS, YPOS      - These ToolTypes are for Window size and position.
        WIDTH, HEIGHT     Ex. XPOS=10
                              YPOS=20
                              WIDTH=400
                              HEIGHT=120



    See @{" Preferences and Settings Priority " LINK "pands"} for further info.

@endnode

@node smartdisp " ReCatIt / Smart Display "

    SMART DISPLAY

    Starting from V2.40, ReCatIt offers a new, great, feature:
    Smart Display.

    In this window, you'll be able to see in real time the changes
    you are making on a certain phrase.

    The use is straigth forward, to open the Smart Display Window
    you have just to select the "Smart Display" option from the
    "ReCatIt Mode" menu (Amiga + D).

    Smart Display Window is one of the good idea that CatEdit 
    implemented and I have stolen and upgraded. ;)


@endnode

